snippet.textDisplay: Out of respect for Stephen's wishes, I won't say everything I want to here. But from the bottom of my heart, I have to say you fucked up. Big time. Danplan is as popular as it is and as great as it used to be because of Stephen. Even when the animation was basic, even when the editing was minimal, even when the budget was low: Stephen attracted the masses with the character he built and spent so much time on. Stephen was the root of Danplan's success, because without him the show becomes stale. Hosuh, for as amazing as he is, needs his counterpart in Stephen for the show to flow. And Daniel, you're the one people never mention when talking favorites. If you left the show, no one would really care. The show could go back to the way it used to be, but without you, and still garner a large following. Good luck in the future, you lost something massive.

snippet.textDisplay: Okay, okay. I feel I should justify myself here. I'm not going to unsubscribe. And this is NOT, repeat NOT, in any favour of Dan. I believe, from what Stephen has so emotionally revealed, that what Daniel did and said is absolutely appalling (as a friend AND a "boss"). BUT, I do love Hosuh, and he DEFINITELY doesn't deserve to be caught in the middle; most likely, he is. (I've been in that place before and it's awful). So that's the reason I will remain a subscriber and continue watching DanPlan's videos- until a point where Hosuh leaves the channel (if he chooses to) as my heart absolutely goes out to him during this current situation. I would urge some of you, to do the same (Daniel and Stephen aren't the only individuals involved, please remember that).
